 Mall manager, Mike Tammadge, said that five men walked into the store and showed a gun to one of the cashiers. They stole R500 out of the till before the were disturbed by something and fled. Police are currently looking for a silver Toyota Corolla. No one was injured in the process. A photo of the getaway car is circulating and community members are asked to look out for it.   Hawks members sent to jail for fraud WATCH: The Place of Refuge – Once a vibrant village, now a ghost town WATCH: Robbery caught on video, police looking for suspects Three counts of poaching in one week – and the toll keeps rising   • Save our standby number (072 248 3855) and send us a WhatsApp message with the words “Add me” to be added to our broadcast list. • Like us on Facebook, follow us on Twitter and Instagram. • Subscribe to our YouTube channel. • Click on the link to subscribe to our bi-weekly newsletter via email. Contact our news room on our 24 hr standby number 072 248 3855, or send a mail to our editor tobie@mobserver.co.za